{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895/events","html_url":"https://github.com/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895","id":791022738,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3OTEwMjI3Mzg=","number":4895,"title":"Standardise the search and fetch APIs of all subclasses of BaseClient","user":{"login":"Cadair","id":1391051,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzOTEwNTE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1391051?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair","html_url":"https://github.com/Cadair","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Cadair/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":123240217,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxMjMyNDAyMTc=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/labels/net","name":"net","color":"c7def8","default":false,"description":"Affects the net submodule"},{"id":2258294576,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwyMjU4Mjk0NTc2","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/labels/Discussion","name":"Discussion","color":"eaa1c1","default":false,"description":"An issue opened for, or undergoing discussion."}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2021-01-21T12:23:46Z","updated_at":"2023-03-15T17:51:43Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"Currently the signatures in the base client are:

```python
    def search(self, *args, **kwargs):

    def fetch(self, query_results, *, path=None, overwrite=False, progress=True,
              max_conn=5, downloader=None, wait=True, **kwargs):
```

A lot of the clients we have make up their own signature, we should decide on a standard signature in the base client and then try and unify the subclasses as much as possible. I propose the following signature for search:

```python
    def search(self, *query, **kwargs):
```

fetch is more complex, there is part of me which thinks a very minimal signature like this:
```
    def fetch(self, *query_results, path=None, downloader=None, wait=True, **kwargs):
```
would be fine and users of individual clients (not Fido) can pass the `overwrite`, `progress` and `max_conn` arguments to the `Downloader()` constructor.

Another option would be to do something like:

```python
     def fetch(self, *query_results, path=None, downloader=None, downloader_kwargs=None, wait=True, **kwargs):
```

Finally, it's important that all clients allow `**kwargs` in both fetch and search so Fido can reliably pass through all kwargs to all clients.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/issues/comments/1470491862","html_url":"https://github.com/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895#issuecomment-1470491862","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunpy/sunpy/issues/4895","id":1470491862,"node_id":"IC_kwDOACEKh85XpezW","user":{"login":"exitflynn","id":37214399,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM3MjE0Mzk5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/37214399?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn","html_url":"https://github.com/exitflynn","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/exitflynn/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-03-15T17:51:43Z","updated_at":"2023-03-15T17:51:43Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"i agree with this and prefer the first version of the fetch signature, the second one seems a teeny bit more limiting. has there been any further discussion on this?","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sunp